args:
When the dunefolk repel the Empire's assault,
their bravery moves Nefaria to reminisce about
her subjects. Then a mysterious dragon calling
himself Horus appears and questions Nefaria,
but when she can offer no reply, he vanishes.
Fear the might of Dyrenell! Haaah!
Did you seriously just hurt Ria?!\nOh, you're gonna PAY!
How bad did he get you? Are you okay?
His blade but grazed my arm—and as this\nbody is fallen long hence, it causes me\nneither pain nor discomfort.
Maybe so, but I still think—
Nadine! Ria! You guys all right?!
We're totes golden. Those big chickens\nall ran back to...wherever chickens live.
Uh, was that a horse noise?
Er, I only meant... I am also totes golden?
Yeah, I'll get her stitched up, but thanks.
If you say so. Oh, and thanks a million\nfor fighting on our behalf.
It was naught—er, NOTHING anyone else\nwouldn't have done. But I do have one\nquery if you can, um, deal?
Know you the reason the Empire went\ncrazypants bananas on this place?
No clue. Our only real notable quality is\nthe power to shape mana. It's something\nwe inherited from our ancestors.
(Ah... My consciousness fades...\nThe end draws nigh...)
Oh, My Queen... 'Tis a price too dear\nyou paid to protect us.
Hurry Her Majesty to safety!\nPermit the Empire no further advance!
(I remember now: I fell in battle against\nthe Empire, and my kingdom with me.)
You okay? You just kinda went\nspace case all of a sudden.
Y-yes, I am well; do not trouble\nyourself overmuch.
You KNOW I've got your back, right?\nLike, with anything?
Wow, you two are really close, huh?\nI'm glad you found a pal like her, Nadine.
Now let's get this place put back together.\nWe've got a festival to kick off!
But you were totes attacked\nnot an hour past!
Yeah, but the damage was pretty light.\nPlus who wants to let a bunch of jerks\nlike that ruin our fun?
You take care of Ria, Nadine.\nI'll see you guys later!
Your people of the dunefolk\nare a brave and hardy line.
Unbroken by adversity, you train your eyes\nupon the horizon and advance with a\nsmile ever upon your lips.
Yeah, it's how we were raised, I guess.\nMy folks were always tellin' me to smile.
Guess we probably got that from our\nancestors, huh?
It was ever such with my people as well.
I would beg a boon of you now, Nadine:\nTeach me to model!
Aye, I've the example of\nthe dunefolk to live up to.
Gotcha! Well, hang on tight, 'cause we're\nabout to bump this thing up to eleven!
Oh, but don't forget you still owe me a\nfestival date on top of the fashion show.
I could scarce neglect that plight.
(Today has proven most diverting; I cannot\nrecall the last festival I so enjoyed.)
(The attack is but hours old, yet already\nfeels long forgot. Truly, they are a most\nimpressive people.)
(Had my kingdom not fallen, perhaps my\npeople might have availed themselves\nof such merrymaking at battle's end.)
If my strength had been but enough...
I am Horus. Answer me this, Queen:\nDid you love your subjects?
The voice from my dream!\nKnow you of me, then?
I would have an answer, Queen:\nDid you love your subjects?
Of course! What love I e'er held,\nI held for them.
Even if that love brought your demise?
Who are you to riddle me so?!
I seek to unravel this contradiction.\nAnd so I ask you once more:
Does a queen unmade for love of her\nsubjects yet cling to that love in death?
You speak as if my people drew the knife\nacross my throat!
I am merely an observer. And with naught\nleft to discern, I see nothing to stay me.
No! Come back! ...Fie, is it possible?\nWere my own people truly the cause\nof my demise?
What happened on the day\nI fled this mortal coil...?
